  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zimbabwe Initial Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ADRA provide food for 130 households (approximately 655 individuals) who have been affected by flooding

Benefiting households will each receive monthly food rations for the following commodities; 
4 kg of cereal per person per month 
2.4 kg pulses/soya mince per person per month and
0.75 ml of vegetable oil per person per month
1kg iodized salt per family</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The tropical depression was characterized by heavy rainfall (with over 100 mm/24 hours) and strong winds which resulted in damages to houses and public buildings, infrastructure, including roads, dams and electricity and agricultural land, thus affecting livelihoods.
These are some of the statistics related to emergency:

Number of homeless people	1,985
Damaged homesteads	2,579
Number of people marooned	1,576
Loss of human lives	246 deaths and 128 reported injuries
Number of health institutions  damaged	5
Number of schools damaged	74
Number of breached small and medium dams	70</narrative>
  </description>
